Pre-Game Insights: Liberia had to dig deep in the Group E curtain-raiser as they fought back from behind to snatch a point against Togo.
Liberia have now gone unbeaten in five straight games across all competitions, claiming three draws and two wins.
Algeria, on the other hand, kicked off their quest for a place in Morocco on a high as they secured a 2-0 victory over Equatorial Guinea.
Algeria have picked up three wins from their four games in Group G of the World Cup qualifiers to sit top of the table, level on nine points with second-placed Mozambique in the playoff spot.
Liberia will need to be at their best against Algeria, who are unbeaten in their last six encounters.
The Greens boast the firepower needed to get the job done and we are tipping them off to secure all three points at the Samuel Kanyon Doe Sports Complex.
